# Band 8 Sample Answer

## Introduction

The bar chart compares how often people in the USA ate at fast-food restaurants in 2003, 2006 and 2013.

**翻译：**
该柱状图比较了美国人在2003年、2006年和2013年去快餐店就餐的频率。

---

## Overview

Overall, the majority of Americans ate fast food either once a week or once or twice a month throughout the period. Eating fast food every day or never doing so remained relatively uncommon in all three years. In addition, there was a noticeable shift from weekly visits towards monthly visits by 2013.

**翻译：**
总体来看，在整个时期内，大多数美国人去快餐店的频率主要集中在“每周一次”或“每月一到两次”。相比之下，“每天吃快餐”以及“从不吃快餐”的人始终占比较小。此外，到2013年，人们的消费习惯明显从“每周一次”逐渐转向“每月一到两次”。

---

## Body Paragraph 1

In 2003, the largest proportion of people ate at fast-food restaurants once a week, accounting for about 31%, while roughly 30% visited such restaurants once or twice a month. The figures for 2006 were similar, although the percentage for weekly visits rose slightly to approximately 33%, making it the highest figure shown on the chart. By contrast, only around 3% to 5% of people ate fast food every day or never consumed it in both years.

**翻译：**
在2003年，比例最高的人群是“每周一次”去快餐店，占约31%；与此同时，大约30%的人每月去一到两次。2006年的情况与之相似，不过“每周一次”的比例略微上升至约33%，成为图表中的最高数据。相比之下，在这两年中，每天吃快餐或从不吃快餐的人仅占约3%到5%。

---

## Body Paragraph 2

By 2013, the pattern had changed slightly. The proportion of people eating fast food once or twice a month increased to around 33%, overtaking weekly customers, whose figure fell to approximately 28%. Meanwhile, the percentage of Americans eating fast food several times a week declined gradually from 17% in 2003 to about 16% in 2013. The proportion of those visiting fast-food restaurants only a few times a year remained fairly stable at around 13% to 15% throughout the period.

**翻译：**
到2013年，这一模式出现了一些变化。每月去一到两次快餐店的人数比例上升至约33%，超过了“每周一次”的消费者，而后者则下降至约28%。与此同时，每周吃几次快餐的美国人比例从2003年的17%逐渐下降至2013年的约16%。而“每年只去几次快餐店”的比例在整个时期内则基本稳定在13%至15%之间。

